auc_table
```

Exploratory analysis reveals several predictors with strong relationships to default. External credit scores (EXT_SOURCE_1, EXT_SOURCE_2, EXT_SOURCE_3) exhibit the strongest separation between defaulters and non-defaulters, indicating high predictive potential. Age and employment duration also show meaningful differences across target classes, with younger and less stably employed applicants more likely to default.

Among categorical variables, education level and asset ownership indicators display notable variation in default rates. These findings suggest that both financial history variables and socio-economic characteristics will be important inputs in subsequent predictive models.

